          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Next Question Correctedness",
          "Probability of Next Question being Correct",
          "297915 EdNet learners",
          "293 tags on EdNet",
          "Sequence of Questions/Answers,\nLMS logs",
          "[Questions, Time of Interactions (Response Time, Lag Time, Explanation Time, Video Lecture Time), Answers]",
          "Most of the current KT approaches do not consider the time spent on different learrning activities. \n\nMoreover, the knowledge is often estimated from sequences of answers (no formal assessment of prior knowledge). Forgetting is also not usually explained. ",
          "The Enhanced Transformer arquitecture does uses multihead attention wherein:\n\n- Queries are the question embeddings\n\n- Keys are embeddings of the sequences of interactions of the students\n\n- Values: Embedding that considers the correctedness of the previous questions.",
          "Authors extract from logs the time spent on different learning activities. \n\nThese are given as input to a Multihead attention layer.",
          "DKT, DKVMN, SAKT, SAINT, SAINT+, Enhanced Transformer",
          "Holdout Method",
          "{Accuracy: 0.8319 - E-Transformer with all time features, AUC: 0.8489 - E-Transformer with all time features}",
          "Authors propose a new architecture called the Enhanced Transformer.\n\nThe model uses multihead atention to receive Questions, Time Spent on Activities and Answers and, when comparing the model against other KT models in the same dataset, the model outperforms all others.\n\nAblation study to check the effect different types of temporal features shows that they do, indeed, increase the performance of the model.",
          "- Holdout method\n\n - Executes test in a single dataset\n\n- Could consider additional temporal features\n\n- Utilization of forgetting behavior does not consider any form of pedagogical grounding.\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
